Check if Two Strings are Rotation of Each Other | Check if one string is a rotated version of another. |

import java.util.*;
class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String str1 = "waterbottle";
        String str2 = "erbottlewat";
        System.out.println("Rotating strings: "+ rotateString(str1,str2));
    }
    public static boolean rotateString(String str1,String str2){
        if(str1.length()!=str2.length()){
            return false;
        }
        String s = str1+str2;
        return s.contains(str2);
    }
}

output:
Rotating strings: true

explanation:
For str1 = "waterbottle" and str2 = "erbottlewat", the process works as follows:
The lengths of both strings are the same, so it moves forward.
Concatenate str1 with itself: "waterbottlewaterbottle".
Check if str2 ("erbottlewat") is a substring of "waterbottlewaterbottle".
Since "erbottlewat" is indeed a substring, the method correctly returns true.
